Shakib, among the elite allrounders in the world, will not be happy with that

commentary: Shakib Al Hasan to R Powell, 2 runs good length on off, and Powell once again makes some room to free his arms. Pulled over to deep midwicket, and a diving effort in the deep may have saved a boundary. But the umpires want to have a second look. Every single run saved counts at this stage.

commentary: Mustafizur Rahman to R Powell, no run good length on leg stump, and Powell misses the leg-side swipe. Hits his front pad, and the lbw appeal is turned down! Looked much closer, but maybe the height saved him. A chance of a run-out as well, as Mushfiqur has a shy at the stumps with Powell outside his crease. But he misses.
